generalfeedback.text:
We can obtain the information that we require by inspecting the graph. We will see later how we can use mathematics in order to obtain this information, however for now looking at the graph, the turning point is the vertex of the graph which is the point \((-1,-2)\). Clearly this is a maximum and the parabola is concave downwards.

The axis of symmetry is the vertical line which passes through the turning point. Therefore it is the line with equation \(x = -1\).

Recall that the roots of the quadratic correspond to the points at which the curve crosses the \(x\)-axis. We can see that on this graph the parabola does not cross the \(x\)-axis, therefore there are no real roots.
